# Lenstules Lens Styles Module

This folder contains an advanced, independent lens styles module for Android apps (Kotlin).  
You can use it in your app **without affecting any existing features**.

## How to Use

1. Copy the entire `Lenstules` folder into your project next to your `app` module.
2. Add this to your `settings.gradle`:
   ```
   include(":Lenstules")
   ```
3. Add this to your `app/build.gradle`:
   ```groovy
   implementation project(":Lenstules")
   implementation "com.google.code.gson:gson:2.10.1"
   implementation "androidx.recyclerview:recyclerview:1.3.2"
   ```
4. Use the Lens Picker in your Activity/Fragment as described below.

## Features

- Lens style picker UI
- Parameter tuning for effects
- Batch processing
- Sharing/import
- AI stub (for future)
- Depth stub (for future)
- Asset editing stub (for future)
- Animation stub (for future)
- Sample assets

## Folder Structure

```
Lenstules/
├── README.md
├── LensProfile.kt
├── LensPickerFragment.kt
├── LensStyleAdapter.kt
├── LensStyle.kt
└── assets/
    ├── sample_lens_1.json
    └── sample_lens_2.json
```

## Usage Example

```kotlin
val picker = LensPickerFragment.newInstance { selectedLens ->
    // Apply the selected lens style
}
picker.show(supportFragmentManager, "lensPicker")
```

